other_tests.procedure_name: Focused Assessment with Sonography for Trauma (FAST)
other_tests.findings: A large amount of intraperitoneal fluid was noted, which could represent blood or ascites.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Comparison with prior imaging (CT and ultrasound) indicated that the fluid on the recent examination was likely blood.

other_tests.findings: High-grade stenosis of the celiac axis with retrograde filling of the common hepatic and splenic arteries through the pancreaticoduodenal arcade and dorsal pancreatic artery was observed.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The angiography confirmed previously noted conditions and showed newly identified aneurysms that were treated successfully with embolization.

other_tests.findings: A large amount of blood was found within the peritoneal cavity and a ruptured pancreaticoduodenal artery aneurysm was identified.
